{#
  Read-only entry row fragment. Returned by cancel-edit and update routes
  to swap back into the .entry-row container via hx-swap="outerHTML".

  Thin wrapper around the shared components/_entry_row.html.jinja2 macro --
  the same row shape used by components/period_log.html.jinja2 and
  components/day_entries.html.jinja2, so the comment toggle + live comment
  count survive an edit/cancel instead of falling back to a stale bare
  memo+pencil shape.

  is_owner and can_comment are always True for these routes (only the owner
  can reach the edit flow), so the pencil button and comment toggle are
  always eligible to render here -- the comment toggle's actual visibility
  still depends on username/slug being set and on entry.comment_count.

  Context:
    activity_id   int            — owning sub-tally
    entry         dict           — hydrated entry (id, occurred_at, memo,
                                    comment_count, ...)
    username      str | None     — the owner's username (for the comment
                                    toggle's `/@{username}/{slug}/...` URL)
    slug          str | None     — the activity's slug
#}
{% from "components/_entry_row.html.jinja2" import entry_row %}

{{ entry_row(entry, activity_id, is_owner=True, can_comment=True, username=username, slug=slug, expand_comment_entry_id=expand_comment_entry_id | default(None)) }}
